Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.55,0:00:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to JW Broadcasting! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.22,0:00:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In this month’s program, \Nwe’ll meet a brother who preaches \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.09,0:00:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Indian Sign Language field. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.89,0:00:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we learn from his view \Nof the challenges he faces \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.76,0:00:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in his assignment? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.43,0:00:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s sheep \Nbelong to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.43,0:00:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This dramatization \Nshows a special way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.64,0:00:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah uses shepherds \Nin the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.37,0:00:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to care for his flock. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.04,0:00:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And have you witnessed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.78,0:00:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the life-changing moment \Nwhen someone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.78,0:00:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,first learns God’s name? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.18,0:00:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see the results of this sister’s \Nlifelong search to know the true God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.19,0:00:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This and much more is ahead \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.09,0:00:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,on the June 2016 edition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.63,0:00:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.61,0:01:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s people have always considered \Nthe studying of his Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.22,0:01:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to be an essential part of life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.89,0:01:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Law to Israel commanded \Nthat the king “must read from [the Law] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.09,0:01:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,all the days of his life, so that he \Nmay learn to fear Jehovah his God.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.03,0:01:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Mayan territories \Nof Yucatán, Mexico, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.83,0:01:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers are helping people \Nlearn to read God’s Word for themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.77,0:01:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,People’s lives change when they \Ncan finally read the Bible on their own \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.38,0:01:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and more readily ‘learn \Nto fear Jehovah their God.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.99,0:01:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One out of every six people on earth \Ndoesn’t know how to read. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.40,0:01:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses \Naround the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.40,0:01:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have organized literacy classes \Nto help such ones.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.67,0:02:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t like to read. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.38,0:02:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to sleep at the meetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.88,0:02:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In our territory, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.89,0:02:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,most people speak the Mayan language, \Nbut very few can read it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.39,0:02:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,On occasion I would give a talk, \Nand when I would \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.56,0:02:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,cite a scripture, \Nmost of the audience would look it up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.56,0:02:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But then I would see \Na blank stare on their faces \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.90,0:02:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because they \Ncouldn’t read the text.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.94,0:02:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was moved \Nto learn how to read \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.74,0:02:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I wanted to learn about Jehovah \Nand study his Word, the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.58,0:02:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So a sister came \Nto my house to teach me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.89,0:02:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Literacy classes are often conducted \Non an individual level. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.89,0:02:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,After a person has had their Bible study, \Nthey can spend some time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.43,0:02:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to practice reading skills. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.46,0:03:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But when \Nthe local elders notice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.80,0:03:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are many \Nthat can benefit from this training, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.40,0:03:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,they can schedule \Na larger class \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.01,0:03:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Kingdom Hall. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.01,0:03:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The study material used \Nfor this purpose is the brochure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.61,0:03:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Apply Yourself to Reading and Writing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.08,0:03:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s available in 30 languages \Nin the Central America branch territory. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.89,0:03:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Other study materials can be used \Nas well, as long as they help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.19,0:03:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the development of the students \Nenrolled in the class.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.30,0:03:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And we use a board \Non which we write, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.30,0:03:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance, words \Nthat are difficult to pronounce. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.43,0:03:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This helps in the reading \Nof complicated words. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.94,0:03:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some who are, \Nwell, very quick learners. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.64,0:03:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, \Nothers go word by word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.78,0:03:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But as they practice, \Nthey start getting the hang of it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.45,0:03:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m good at masonry work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.89,0:04:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but learning to read \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.36,0:04:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is not easy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.36,0:04:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading at his age \Nis a big challenge.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to understand \Nthat each student learns differently. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.70,0:04:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With some, \Nyou need to be very patient.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.41,0:04:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The first word \NI learned to write was Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.41,0:04:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“It’s like this,” I tell him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.91,0:04:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, “It’s ‘cause \Nyou’re not being patient with me!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.05,0:04:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a sense of humor \Nis a big help in the learning process, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.32,0:04:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so as not to focus \Non errors and mistakes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.42,0:04:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Since 1946, when records \Nbegan being taken in Mexico, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.49,0:04:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 152,000 people \Nhave learned to read and write, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.93,0:04:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks to these training efforts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.80,0:04:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The Secretary of Public Education \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.74,0:04:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in the State of Mexico \Nhas recognized the work and the great help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.37,0:04:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,these literacy classes \Nhave been to the local citizens. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.51,0:04:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The skills they learn \Nhelp in their day-to-day life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.11,0:04:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but also it helps them \Nto learn more about Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.58,0:05:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be able to teach others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.29,0:05:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to have to memorize \Neverything I was going to say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.39,0:05:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but now I can read \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.39,0:05:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,short scriptures to people \Ndirectly from the Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.30,0:05:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,As the students progress \Nin the class, they demonstrate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.74,0:05:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the words found \Nat 1 Timothy 4:15, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.67,0:05:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which says in part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.61,0:05:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that your advancement \Nmay be plainly seen by all people.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.28,0:05:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And these benefits \Nare plainly seen in the students.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband was an alcoholic, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.28,0:05:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,he smoked, \Nand he used bad language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.69,0:05:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But he made big changes \Nin his life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.69,0:05:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see that this training \Nhas been a big help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.33,0:05:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We really see \Nthese great blessings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.17,0:05:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading helped me \Nto get baptized.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.97,0:05:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Helping other people \Nto improve their reading skills \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.34,0:06:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,makes me feel very happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.54,0:06:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel great because I see \Non their face the joy they get \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.31,0:06:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from reading and understanding \Nthe information.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.32,0:06:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’ve benefited so much. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.72,0:06:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.16,0:06:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,now we read the Bible \Ntogether as a family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.43,0:06:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes me very happy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.70,0:06:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re more united as a family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.30,0:06:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our children \Nrespect my husband more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.47,0:06:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like the father he is.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.44,0:06:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I’m a ministerial servant.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.84,0:06:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When I go preaching \Ndoor to door, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.78,0:06:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,some people say, \N“I don’t know how to read.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.12,0:06:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But then I tell them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.32,0:06:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“I didn’t know either, \Nbut I learned about Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can too!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.69,0:06:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If I learned to read, \Nanybody can.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Our theme for this month \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is “Consider, Incite, and Encourage \NOne Another All the More So.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.13,0:07:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,JW Broadcasting\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.66,0:07:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,—why do we enjoy it so much? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.46,0:07:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of you have expressed \Nhow the monthly broadcast draws you closer\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.14,0:07:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to our brothers and sisters \Nand to Jehovah’s organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.27,0:07:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re homebound or isolated, \Nyou especially treasure these programs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.28,0:07:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, while we appreciate \Nthe advances in technology \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.88,0:07:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that have made all of this possible, \Nwe know that your sincere desire \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.29,0:07:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be present \Nwith your brothers and sisters in person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.49,0:07:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at our congregation meetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.96,0:08:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses \Naround the world share this feeling. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.16,0:08:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In northern Finland, for example, \Nwinters are especially cold, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.17,0:08:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,even by Finnish standards. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.17,0:08:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, temperatures plummet \Nto minus 50 degrees Celsius, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.34,0:08:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or minus 58 degrees Fahrenheit! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Under those conditions, \Nit’s very difficult to drive, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.88,0:08:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,much less walk long distances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.28,0:08:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, the brothers love \Nto gather together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.82,0:08:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How do they manage it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.82,0:08:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In one small village, there is a brother \Nwho lives near the Kingdom Hall \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.96,0:08:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and has a warm garage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.09,0:08:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,On meeting nights, he uses his car \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.23,0:08:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring each family \Nin the congregation to the hall. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.63,0:08:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he parks in his garage and runs \Nthe short distance back to the Kingdom Hall.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.44,0:08:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When the meeting is over, he returns \Nall the friends safely to their homes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.44,0:08:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Bible, \Ngatherings for pure worship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.18,0:08:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,were occasions for personal association \Nwith fellow believers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.72,0:08:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Such association required travel \Nto a designated place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.69,0:09:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This involved work, \Nsacrifice, even risk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.49,0:09:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider what is stated \Nat Exodus 34:24. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.50,0:09:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This verse has to do with the command \Nthat every Israelite male \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.04,0:09:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,should gather three times a year \Nfor the festivals in Jerusalem. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.44,0:09:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What would that mean \Nin practical terms? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.38,0:09:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn’t the nation \Nbe left vulnerable to attack\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.65,0:09:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,if no men were left \Nto guard the land?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.18,0:09:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And if word spread \Namong the surrounding nations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.65,0:09:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that practically everyone \Ncongregated in Jerusalem \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.19,0:09:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,three times a year, \Nlike clockwork, year after year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.19,0:09:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn’t it be just a matter of time \Nbefore some invading army \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.13,0:09:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,would come \Nand pillage an Israelite city? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.13,0:09:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,At Exodus 34:24, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.03,0:09:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we find \NJehovah’s remarkable answer: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.30,0:09:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“For I will drive the nations \Naway from before you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.47,0:09:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will enlarge your territory, \Nand nobody will desire,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.15,0:09:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, even desire, “your land \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.62,0:10:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“while you are going up to see \Nthe face of Jehovah your God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.12,0:10:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,three times a year.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.12,0:10:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah kept that promise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.26,0:10:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a historical fact \Nthat from 1513 B.C.E. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.26,0:10:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way down to 66 C.E. \Nno foreign nation ever came \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.30,0:10:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to invade Israelite territory \Nduring those three annual festivals. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.11,0:10:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah placed high value \Non having his people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.44,0:10:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,gather together \Nin the same space. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.18,0:10:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Christian era, \Nthe apostle Paul wrote \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.32,0:10:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Corinthians 14:23 \Nabout ‘the whole congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.59,0:10:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,coming together to one place.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.16,0:10:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, although modern broadcasting \Ntechnology didn’t exist in those days, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.93,0:10:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,there were other viable methods \Nof communicating, such as writing letters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.93,0:10:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that didn’t require people to be physically \Npresent in the same location.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.14,0:10:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, the apostle John, \Nthough a capable writer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.34,0:11:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,preferred face-to-face interchange \Nwith fellow Christians \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.04,0:11:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,as he expressed \Nat 2 John 12.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.08,0:11:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Or consider what is stated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.08,0:11:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,at Job 1:6: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.65,0:11:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now the day came \Nwhen the sons of the true God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.26,0:11:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,entered to take their station \Nbefore Jehovah.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.86,0:11:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Job 2:1 speaks \Nof another such day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.67,0:11:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Just imagine! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.67,0:11:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Here Jehovah himself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.67,0:11:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,though having all conceivable methods \Nof communication at his disposal, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.71,0:11:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,set specific days \Nfor his spirit creatures in heaven \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to assemble \Nin his immediate presence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.85,0:11:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly, the Scriptures encourage \Nregular personal association \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.65,0:11:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with fellow servants of God.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.65,0:11:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Virtual attendance through modern \Ncommunication technology has value, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.13,0:11:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re happy to use it, \Nbut it’s no substitute for being together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And why not? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.53,0:12:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of what association \Nwith the congregation achieves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.27,0:12:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not just that we receive nutritious \Nand varied spiritual food. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.47,0:12:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Meetings inform us, \Nbut so does JW Broadcasting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.81,0:12:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Meetings encourage us, \Nbut so does JW Broadcasting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.28,0:12:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Fellow Christians who offer comments \Nand sing from the heart build us up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.02,0:12:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet we can hear that also \Non JW Broadcasting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.02,0:12:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s when we’re together\N—all together in one place—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.03,0:12:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that others can hear us \Nand draw encouragement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.83,0:12:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,from our heartfelt convictions, \Nour smile, our handshake. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.47,0:12:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Meetings give us opportunities \Nto show our brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.07,0:12:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that we esteem them \Nas worthy of our time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.28,0:12:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,attention, and concern. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.11,0:12:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why we go and visit our brothers \Nwho are homebound or isolated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.25,0:12:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because we want to show them \Nthat we love them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.52,0:12:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, in a special way, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.93,0:13:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,our meetings bring us \Nunder the influence of holy spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.46,0:13:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At Revelation 2:7, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.40,0:13:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the glorified Jesus said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.34,0:13:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let the one \Nwho has an ear hear \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.81,0:13:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,what the spirit says \Nto the congregations.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.21,0:13:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We need that spirit \Nto help us resist temptation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.98,0:13:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to embolden and equip us \Nfor the ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.05,0:13:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and to enable us \Nto make sound decisions.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.65,0:13:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, there’s a reason \Nto attend meetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.46,0:13:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s even more important \Nthan the pleasant company, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.39,0:13:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the peaceful atmosphere, \Nthe genuine refreshment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.30,0:13:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of belonging, \Nthe opportunities to give, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.37,0:13:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or even the fact that meetings \Nare a means by which \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.57,0:13:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we receive \NJehovah’s holy spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.77,0:13:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The key reason \Nwhy we gather together \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.51,0:13:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is stated at Psalm 26:12: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.11,0:13:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“My foot is standing \Non level ground; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.75,0:13:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the great congregation, \NI will praise Jehovah.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the principal reason \Nwhy we gather together in person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.66,0:14:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is to give Jehovah what he deserves\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.73,0:14:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—praise, glory, yes, worship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.73,0:14:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Our meeting attendance \Nshows Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.40,0:14:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that we want to draw close \Nto him and his Son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.14,0:14:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In his abundant love, Jehovah invites \Nmany more to serve him and keep living. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.54,0:14:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he lives eternally, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.54,0:14:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah can nurture \Nthose relationships forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.41,0:14:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Adversary can offer \Nno such hope of endless life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.65,0:14:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so he promotes selfishness, \Npride, and other negative traits \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.72,0:14:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that isolate people from one another, \Neven when they are in the same room, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.99,0:14:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,engaged in the same activities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.46,0:14:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast, our great God \Nis drawing his people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.56,0:14:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,closer to himself, \Nto his Son, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.43,0:14:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and to one another \Nso that we “may all be one,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.37,0:14:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jesus prayed \Nas recorded at John 17:21.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.84,0:14:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s not just the act \Nof converging \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.68,0:14:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on the same location \Nthat unites us either. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.55,0:15:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of people coexist in the same space \Nwhen they go to a market, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.48,0:15:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,attend a sporting event, \Nor use public transportation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.85,0:15:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Crowding of itself \Ndoes not equate with unity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.36,0:15:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes the true \NChristian congregation different? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.36,0:15:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how Hebrews chapter 10, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.70,0:15:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 24 and 25 \Nanswers this question. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.37,0:15:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here we find \Nthe divinely inspired standard \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.31,0:15:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for all our gatherings: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.04,0:15:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“And let us \Nconsider one another so as to incite \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.65,0:15:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“to love and fine works, \Nnot forsaking our meeting together, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.65,0:15:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“as some have the custom, \Nbut encouraging one another, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.19,0:15:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“and all the more so as you see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.92,0:15:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the day drawing near.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.76,0:15:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what does it mean \Nto “consider one another”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.56,0:15:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean \N“to incite to love and fine works”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.90,0:15:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And in what way might we \N‘encourage one another’? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.90,0:15:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The verb “consider” \Ncould also be rendered \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.31,0:16:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“be concerned about; \Npay attention to.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.11,0:16:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So when \Nwe “consider one another,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.58,0:16:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we show interest \Nthat goes far beyond a brief greeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.12,0:16:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we pay careful attention \Nto one another, we’re better prepared \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.85,0:16:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to incite, that is, to motivate one another, \Nto stir one another to action. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.79,0:16:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And how might we do this? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.06,0:16:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by making comparisons \Nor shaming our brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.40,0:16:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for that would hardly be \N“encouraging one another,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.73,0:16:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we endeavor to lift one another’s hearts \Nwhen we’re together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.27,0:16:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we do this \Nto the best of our ability, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.41,0:16:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then we can be confident \Nthat Jehovah’s spirit will do the rest, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.08,0:16:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and that our brothers \Nwill feel strengthened.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.41,0:16:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s evident, then, \Nthat true worship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.85,0:16:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,means participation; \Nit requires a response. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.65,0:16:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Another noteworthy example of this \Nis the encouragement we both give \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.33,0:16:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and receive when we sing together \Nwith our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.16,0:16:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In ancient Israel, \Nat times they had a chorus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.17,0:17:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,such as the one described \Nin Nehemiah chapter 12 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.64,0:17:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that we talked about \Nin our midweek meeting back in February. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.77,0:17:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Much of Israel’s group singing \Nwas antiphonal, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.91,0:17:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, some of the singers \Nprompted others to respond. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.25,0:17:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, Psalm 106 \Nwhich begins and ends with the words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.98,0:17:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“Praise Jah!” or “Hallelujah!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.39,0:17:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,encouraged the people \Nto say in response: “Amen!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.36,0:17:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 136 was written \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.36,0:17:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to allow for different choruses \Nto answer one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.23,0:17:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now just imagine \Nresponding choruses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.44,0:17:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,singing these alternating lines: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.01,0:17:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Give thanks to Jehovah, for he is good; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.94,0:17:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“his loyal love endures forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.01,0:17:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“Give thanks to the God of gods, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“for his loyal love endures forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.69,0:17:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“Give thanks to the Lord of lords, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.49,0:17:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for his loyal love endures forever.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.29,0:17:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And on it went for 26 verses!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.96,0:18:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,To this day, \Nsinging demonstrates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.03,0:18:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,our heartfelt response \Nto the goodness of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.17,0:18:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What a joy it is to sing \Nin company with others who are moved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.64,0:18:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to pour out the depths \Nof their feelings to Jehovah! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.31,0:18:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And now at our Kingdom Halls, \Nwe’re accompanied by orchestral renderings\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.38,0:18:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of many of our songs\N—another reason to sing out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.52,0:18:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,at our midweek\Nand weekend meetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.72,0:18:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And speaking of the midweek meeting, \Nhow are you enjoying the new format? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.72,0:18:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,More of the program is devoted \Nto delving into the Bible itself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.93,0:18:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Time spent on preparing us \Nfor our public ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.33,0:18:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,focuses more than ever \Non situations we face in field service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.34,0:18:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And the meetings move along \Nat a satisfying pace.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.27,0:18:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, JW Broadcasting \Nis a wonderful blessing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.28,0:18:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a powerful means to talk to \Nand fortify our brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.28,0:18:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,around the world\N—simultaneously. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.95,0:19:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, nothing can replace \Nthe experience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.02,0:19:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of worshipping Jehovah \Nin concert \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.22,0:19:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with our fellow servants of God \Nat congregation meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.09,0:19:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,When a meeting concludes \Nand we lift our heads \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.83,0:19:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,after the final prayer, \Nwe find ourselves surrounded \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.37,0:19:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,by others who love Jehovah \Nand support his sovereignty.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.78,0:19:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,These important benefits \Nare detailed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.18,0:19:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in the April 2016 \Nstudy article \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.25,0:19:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why Should We Meet \NTogether for Worship?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.12,0:19:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This month, we’re studying \Nthat article worldwide. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.85,0:19:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, in October, \Nwe begin a special campaign \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.26,0:19:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to invite the public \Nto our meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.39,0:19:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do not yet regularly associate \Nwith Jehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.06,0:19:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or if you travel away \Nfrom your congregation, use jw.org \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.74,0:19:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to find a meeting you can attend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.00,0:19:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Click: “About Us,” “Meetings,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.97,0:19:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and “Find a Location Near You” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.31,0:19:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or simply scroll to the bottom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.51,0:19:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of any jw.org page \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.72,0:20:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and click “Attend Our Meetings.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.58,0:20:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At our meetings, \Nyou’ll experience what it means \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.62,0:20:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to consider, incite, and ‘encourage \None another all the more so \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.59,0:20:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as we see \Nthe day drawing near.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.83,0:20:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve discussed \Nvital ways we benefit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.67,0:20:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,when we come together \Nfor worship at Christian meetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.84,0:20:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What many notice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.84,0:20:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,when they first attend meetings \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.18,0:20:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is that they hear \NGod’s name, Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.05,0:20:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In this life story, \NSoten Yoeun relates the impact \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.52,0:20:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that learning God’s name \Nhad on her \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.12,0:20:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,after surviving \Nthe killing fields of Cambodia.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.69,0:20:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On the killing fields \Nin Cambodia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.53,0:20:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed to God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.64,0:20:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I didn’t know his name.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.85,0:21:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a very young girl, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.42,0:21:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,they separated our family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.82,0:21:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and they put me \Nto work in the rice field \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.52,0:21:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,from five in the morning \Ntill nine in the evening.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.99,0:21:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see \Nsome other children that get killed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.86,0:21:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you really desperately cry \Nfor help inside. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.13,0:21:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You always think \Nthat you are next. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.14,0:21:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But in my heart I always believed \Nthat there had to be a true God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.14,0:21:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere, somehow \Nthat can help me get through this.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.21,0:21:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One year later, \Nmy family decided to escape Cambodia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.92,0:21:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We walk close to six \Nor seven months to Thailand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.86,0:21:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have 20 brothers and sisters\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.53,0:21:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—only 4 of us survived.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.70,0:22:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a blind aunt that holds \Non my shoulder all the time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.38,0:22:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But one day, we got caught. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.01,0:22:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,As they start shooting, \NI push my aunt down to the ground \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.02,0:22:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to pretend \Nthat we are dead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.76,0:22:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I get up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.76,0:22:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea \Nwhere my parent was.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.10,0:22:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We spent \Nmany months in the jungle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.23,0:22:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As I try to survive, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.24,0:22:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I eat whatever I can find, \Nand I also help my auntie to survive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.91,0:22:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,One day when I go \Nout to look for food, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.31,0:22:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I walked so far away \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.11,0:22:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t find my way back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.65,0:22:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I start crying really hard \Nunderneath a tree \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.92,0:22:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and look up to the sky \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.66,0:22:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and pray to the true God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.59,0:23:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I was raised as a child \Nto pray to Buddhas. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.60,0:23:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But on this night \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.60,0:23:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,when I start praying, \NI specifically said \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.87,0:23:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’m not praying \Nto Buddha\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.74,0:23:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—I’m praying \Nto the true God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.58,0:23:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.58,0:23:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“True God, \Nif you are really here, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.35,0:23:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“please help me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.28,0:23:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“because I am really scared \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.59,0:23:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’m hungry \Nand I’m cold.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.52,0:23:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,After I pray, I just fall to sleep \Nunder the big tree.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.03,0:23:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, I make it \Ninto the refugee camp in Thailand, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.57,0:23:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was reunited \Nwith my family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.80,0:23:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We lived in the refugee camp \Nin Thailand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.74,0:23:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for about ten years \Nbefore we come to United States. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.08,0:23:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,My searching for the true God, \Nit didn’t stop there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.02,0:23:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried to go \Nto different churches, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.05,0:24:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but we \Ndidn’t understand anything.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,One day when I come home \Nfrom school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.13,0:24:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I met this gentlemen \Nnamed Herold, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.53,0:24:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and he asked if he can talk \Nto me about God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.83,0:24:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree because I saw he have a Bible; \Nhe must be a good man. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.37,0:24:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When he talked to me, \NI tried to pay attention so hard, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.37,0:24:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I still didn’t understand \Nwhat he was saying.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.91,0:24:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And he went very slow.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.72,0:24:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he said, “Your name?” \NI said, “My name Soten.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.75,0:24:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he said, “Your name, Soten; \Nmy name is Herold. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.56,0:24:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s name, Jehovah.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.89,0:24:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought \Nthat God had name.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.50,0:24:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And ever since that day on, \NI never forget Jehovah’s name. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.57,0:24:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s superglued in my heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.04,0:24:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave me his phone number. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.77,0:24:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He say he gonna ask his wife \Nto stop by someday, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.68,0:24:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but then I move away \Nfrom where I lived.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.95,0:25:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I didn’t do \Nthe truth at that time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.55,0:25:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I always pray to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.69,0:25:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,After I learned God’s name, \NI went back to the church. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.69,0:25:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The priest would start out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.09,0:25:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with “heavenly Father” \Nbut leave out Jehovah’s name. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.36,0:25:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So I raised my hand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.60,0:25:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him, “Sir, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.27,0:25:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“when you pray “heavenly Father,” \Nwhy don’t you say \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.74,0:25:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘heavenly Father, Jehovah’?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.47,0:25:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why you not using God’s name?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.58,0:25:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he told me that God \Ndoes not force me to be here, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.51,0:25:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so I’m welcomed to leave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.32,0:25:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or stay if I want. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.32,0:25:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So because I realized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.32,0:25:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that they don’t use \NJehovah’s name, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.46,0:25:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I left and never returned.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.16,0:25:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And after many years, \NI tried to call Herold, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.27,0:25:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but no one \Npicked up the phone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.67,0:25:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I leave a message. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.74,0:26:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping \Nthat they remembered me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.61,0:26:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Two weeks later, \NHerold comes to my door, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.52,0:26:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but at the time, I was working at night \Nand asleep during the day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.89,0:26:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But Herold never give up; \Nhe come back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.23,0:26:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I keep on praying \Nto Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.96,0:26:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,asking for someone \Nto knock on my door. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.63,0:26:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, one day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.10,0:26:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I open the door, \Nand when I saw him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.94,0:26:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I almost couldn’t talk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.94,0:26:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was teared up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.74,0:26:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so happy to see him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.28,0:26:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is the man \Nwho introduced me to Jehovah’s name.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.78,0:26:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, I start \Nto study with a sister, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.95,0:26:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and she helped me \Ngrow spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.12,0:26:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To know that you have \Na heavenly Father \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.63,0:26:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that cares about you\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.03,0:26:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,—that was \Nthe best feeling on earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.97,0:27:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes me want to know more about him\N—want to learn more about him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.44,0:27:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I would ask questions: \N“Did he like this? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.77,0:27:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he like that?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.78,0:27:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when I go \Nto the Kingdom Hall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.11,0:27:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear Jehovah’s name \Nso many times. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.22,0:27:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel, that’s it! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.25,0:27:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I found my place.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.32,0:27:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I got baptized in 2013. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.13,0:27:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My blind aunt that I help her \Nsurvive through the jungle, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.96,0:27:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,she’s still living until today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.77,0:27:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that I can get a chance \Nto talk to her about Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.94,0:27:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that was a blessing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.54,0:27:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can’t stress enough \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.54,0:27:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how wonderful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.81,0:27:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and big privilege \Nthat I receive from Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.08,0:27:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—just to know \Nwho he is and to learn \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.02,0:27:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is true God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.72,0:27:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He have a name, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.46,0:27:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and his name is Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.14,0:28:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Yoeun \Nstill carries painful memories \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.94,0:28:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,from what she and her family suffered \Nbecause of man’s ruthless wars. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.41,0:28:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But she now has hope \Nfor the future \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.95,0:28:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the comfort of knowing \Nher heavenly Father, Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.55,0:28:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,—something we \Nall share with her. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.49,0:28:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Yoeun has the added joy \Nof worshipping the true God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.56,0:28:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,together with her husband \Nand young daughter.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.56,0:28:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When we’re at our meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.89,0:28:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we help the congregation \Nto stay close together, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.33,0:28:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,part of the “one flock” \Nthat follows the “one shepherd.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.07,0:28:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization, \Nnote the way in which one young man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.74,0:28:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,receives Jehovah’s love \Nthrough faithful undershepherds.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.75,0:28:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I always loved music. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.75,0:28:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I got my first guitar \Nwhen I was 15, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.85,0:29:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and since then it’s been my way \Nof expressing myself.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.92,0:29:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When they asked, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.93,0:29:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Dave, do you want \Nto join the band?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.00,0:29:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t have to think twice.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.50,0:29:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Making music, \Nthat’s all that really mattered to me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.70,0:29:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought being a musician \Nwould make me happy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.27,0:29:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is the path \NI followed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.88,0:29:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Only it is not \Nwhat I thought it to be.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.79,0:29:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I work here \Nduring the day to pay the bills. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.73,0:29:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought my life \Nwould turn out better. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.23,0:29:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But something was missing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.44,0:29:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of being happy, \NI just felt lost.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.71,0:30:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I’m distracted!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.42,0:30:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They are friendly \Nand look happy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.73,0:30:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave me a tract and said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.40,0:30:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“Many people are searching \Nfor true happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.14,0:30:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you \Nare one of them.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.51,0:30:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This could help.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.45,0:30:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I quickly wrote down my address \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.09,0:30:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and asked whether they would mind \Npassing by after I finished my shift.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.93,0:30:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I was searching all right.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.97,0:30:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, the answers \Nwere in front of me all along.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.98,0:31:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How come I only get it now?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.59,0:31:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.06,0:31:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.89,0:31:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I never gave \Nthe truth a chance.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.90,0:31:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Roy did come as promised. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.01,0:31:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him, \N“I’m a baptized brother.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.12,0:31:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He really listened to me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.65,0:31:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he shared Psalm 100:3:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.99,0:31:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“Know that Jehovah is God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.16,0:31:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“He is the one who made us, \Nand we belong to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.93,0:32:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We are his people \Nand the sheep of his pasture.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.50,0:32:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Bible, \NJehovah is likened to a shepherd. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.47,0:32:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows \Nevery single one of his sheep, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.34,0:32:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he knows \Nwhen one goes missing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.88,0:32:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A lost sheep is not a lost cause; \Nit still belongs to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.68,0:32:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah \Ndoesn’t spare any efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.89,0:32:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in searching for it \Nuntil he finds it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.56,0:32:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was like one of those lost sheep. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.77,0:32:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I still belonged \Nto Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.80,0:32:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has never \Nforgotten about me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.38,0:32:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Roy promised \Nwe would keep in touch \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.55,0:32:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and invited me \Nto the Sunday meeting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.76,0:33:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I was nervous \Nthat morning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.93,0:33:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to look my best.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.81,0:33:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Roy and Matthew \Nwere waiting for me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.44,0:33:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,giving me a warm welcome\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.28,0:33:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—something I’ll never forget.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.25,0:33:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How I missed this! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.12,0:33:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is indeed \NJehovah’s congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.73,0:33:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where I belong.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.00,0:33:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth has never \Nbeen so clear to me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.58,0:33:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How I enjoy the close company\Nof my brothers and sisters!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.98,0:33:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What I enjoy most \Nis helping others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.99,0:34:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to find our loving Father, \NJehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.33,0:34:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah’s help, \NI will never be lost again.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.87,0:34:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The November 2015 broadcast stressed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.88,0:34:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is no better place to be \Nthan in Jehovah’s protective arms. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.81,0:34:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who have drifted away from Jehovah\Nwere then, and are still now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.29,0:34:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,warmly encouraged \Nto act without delay. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.69,0:34:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As we saw depicted, \NJehovah provides shepherds \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.03,0:34:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who care for his sheep \Nand lovingly guide them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.63,0:34:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,back into his organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.26,0:34:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When the preaching work \Nwas getting started \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.33,0:34:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in such countries \Nas South Korea, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.74,0:34:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah often used missionaries \Nto help strengthen our brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.77,0:34:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In an archived interview, \NBrother Chong-il Park \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.91,0:34:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,describes the effect \Nthis had on his sacred service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.11,0:35:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it prepared him \Nfor the trials he would face.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.69,0:35:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,From 1939 on, \Nour brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.82,0:35:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,didn’t have any contact \Nwith Jehovah’s organization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.49,0:35:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and they thought \Nthat no organization existed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.86,0:35:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, in 1948, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.00,0:35:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a brother \Nread from a newspaper \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.10,0:35:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,about the activity \Nof Watchtower Society. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.24,0:35:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And it surprised the brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.18,0:35:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So brothers wrote the Society, \Nand the Society \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.31,0:35:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was so happy \Nhearing from Korean brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.72,0:35:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and they answered \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.78,0:35:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with many booklets \Nin Korean. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.26,0:35:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,There were \Ntwo different reactions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.99,0:35:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Some brothers was excited \Nabout preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.09,0:35:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, \Nanother group questioned: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.60,0:35:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Is that true organization \Nof Jehovah?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.57,0:35:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,First missionary group\N—Brother and Sister Steele—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.71,0:36:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,arrived on August 9, 1949. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.31,0:36:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All the questions \Nwere answered \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.51,0:36:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by Brother Steele, \Nand then \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.12,0:36:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,right away \Nbrothers were preaching \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.12,0:36:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in unity.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.96,0:36:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I began pioneering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.39,0:36:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in January 1950. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.86,0:36:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then in March 1950, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.40,0:36:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,six more missionaries \Narrived from Gilead School. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.97,0:36:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We had only one congregation \Nin Seoul. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.90,0:36:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the missionaries \Nwere busy for many Bible studies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.24,0:36:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So many interested persons \Ncoming to the meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.68,0:36:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The public talk was arranged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.08,0:36:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in school auditorium\N—first time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.49,0:36:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And there were \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.76,0:36:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,over 360 people attended, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.43,0:36:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,whereas the publishers was \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.40,0:37:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,about 60.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.34,0:37:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The same day, \NKorean War broke out, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.44,0:37:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the missionaries \Nhad to leave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.38,0:37:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,on 27th of June \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.65,0:37:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to Japan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.85,0:37:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then our brothers \Nhad to take refuge \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.66,0:37:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to southern part \Nof Korea. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.62,0:37:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hiding \Nin the country. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.96,0:37:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then few days later, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.96,0:37:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the secret police \Nfrom Communist found us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.50,0:37:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We explained to him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.54,0:37:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as a Christian \Nwe cannot participate in the war, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.34,0:37:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so we had \Nto hide ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.05,0:37:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he says: “Well, \NI do not know much about religion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.45,0:37:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“so I better take \None of my friends \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.85,0:37:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“who knows about religion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.89,0:37:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“So I will \Ncome back tomorrow. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.23,0:38:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t leave from here.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.36,0:38:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, \Nwe waited until next day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.30,0:38:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and he came with another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.67,0:38:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So I started preaching \Nfrom the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.94,0:38:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,about why \Nthis war broke out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.08,0:38:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the many problems \Nin the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.08,0:38:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and so on, \Nbecause the fulfillment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.35,0:38:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jesus’ prophecy \Nin Matthew 24. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.38,0:38:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they say, \N“Well, thank you very much \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.59,0:38:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for your preaching.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.52,0:38:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then say, “Goodbye.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.66,0:38:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Then two days later, \Nthe latter one came \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.10,0:38:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,with another friend \Nso that we could preach to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.57,0:38:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,During three months \Nthey were staying in Seoul, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.04,0:38:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and, in fact, \Nthey protected us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.78,0:38:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I was picked \Nby South Korean army \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.85,0:38:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve the back support \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.95,0:39:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of the military \Nin front line to carry arms \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.46,0:39:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to the soldiers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.59,0:39:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which I could not accept, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.20,0:39:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so I refused it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.73,0:39:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.47,0:39:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was beaten.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.04,0:39:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.18,0:39:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this company has to move \Nto another place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.28,0:39:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I hide myself \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.28,0:39:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in behind the ceiling \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.78,0:39:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they don’t notice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.75,0:39:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,when they leave the place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.36,0:39:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next morning \Nwhen I came down, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.19,0:39:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there was nothing left. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.00,0:39:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I walked on one street, \Ntoward one direction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.00,0:39:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I found a sign \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.74,0:39:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that said \N“International Bible Students Association.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.01,0:39:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So I stayed with the brothers \Nfor six months.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.51,0:40:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Steele \Ncame back from Japan \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.12,0:40:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,by himself to take care \Nof the brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.69,0:40:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1952, Brother Steele \Nrecommended me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.29,0:40:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to Gilead School. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.10,0:40:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So that I was invited \Nin 22nd class. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.10,0:40:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So I took the steps \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.27,0:40:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the passport. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.87,0:40:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the government find out \Nthat I didn’t serve in military. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.81,0:40:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They gave me draft notice \Ninstead of passport. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.92,0:40:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to stand \Nfor the neutrality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.45,0:40:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of going to Gilead School, \Nwhich made me to be confined \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.93,0:40:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in military prison \Nfor two years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.50,0:40:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then 1958, I was enrolled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.63,0:40:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in Gilead School in 32nd class. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.30,0:40:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.84,0:41:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that great Gilead School training. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.38,0:41:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Since my job in the branch, \Nespecially in translation work\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.38,0:41:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,—and translation work \Ninvolves much deep knowledge—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.59,0:41:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the Gilead training \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.19,0:41:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,has certainly helped \Nin translation work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.46,0:41:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The real appreciation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.03,0:41:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,about the truth \Nand the organization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.57,0:41:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers’ qualities, \Nthe humbleness and meekness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.57,0:41:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly it helped me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.34,0:41:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to follow the examples \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.41,0:41:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to apply \Nin the full-time service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.82,0:41:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you note what Brother Park \Nsaid he appreciated most \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.29,0:41:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,even after enduring persecution \Nand prison for his faith? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.23,0:41:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the Christlike qualities \Nof his brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.16,0:41:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the training he received \Nfrom Jehovah’s organization\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.03,0:42:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,—another example of the benefits \Nthat result from our meeting together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.70,0:42:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’d like to find more ways \Nto imitate Brother Park’s faith, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.57,0:42:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you can read his life story \Nbeginning on page 12 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.31,0:42:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of the December 2008 issue \Nof Awake!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.25,0:42:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Like many older ones \Nbefore them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.92,0:42:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,younger brothers and sisters \Nare taking on challenging assignments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.45,0:42:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that bring them \Nrich spiritual rewards. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.56,0:42:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We go next to India to hear \Nfrom Brother Francis Rodrigues. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.36,0:42:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s using his training \Nfrom the School for Kingdom Evangelizers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.03,0:42:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to teach people \Nin the Indian Sign Language field.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.18,0:46:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Rodrigues searches for those \Nrightly disposed for everlasting life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.59,0:46:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,wherever he can find them \Ndespite the obstacles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.26,0:46:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you may have noted \Nthat his joy comes from directing people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.93,0:46:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to the congregation to be part \Nof our true spiritual brotherhood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.06,0:46:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That example is repeated millions \Nof times over through the diligent efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.67,0:46:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of publishers and pioneers \Naround the world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.27,0:46:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not examine your ministry \Nto find ways to help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.88,0:46:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,yet more people to build \Na good relationship with Jehovah?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.95,0:46:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As we’ve seen \Njust in this program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.28,0:46:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,examples of faith \Ncome in a variety of forms. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.22,0:46:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In the April 2016 program, \Nwe saw the first two installments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.62,0:46:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in the series \N“Viewpoints on the Origin of Life.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.26,0:46:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll now enjoy two more examples of those\Nwhose backgrounds in scientific study \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.27,0:47:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,enabled them to cultivate \Nstrong faith in the Creator.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.68,0:47:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My name \Nis Rocío Picado Herrero. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.55,0:47:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I studied chemistry \Nat the University of Salamanca, in Spain. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.82,0:47:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I specialize in organic chemistry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.09,0:47:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This field focuses \Non the study of the carbon atom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.69,0:47:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the compounds \Nthat are derived from this atom.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.90,0:47:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I believed that life \Ncame about through evolution. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.37,0:47:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember seeing a picture \Nin a natural science book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.44,0:47:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that depicted the embryos \Nof different vertebrates, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.77,0:47:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the early stages of development, \Nthe similarities were outstanding. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.61,0:47:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I started studying \Nat the university, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.78,0:47:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I began studying \Nin detail the process \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.18,0:47:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,on which \Nthe evolution theory is based. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.99,0:47:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,To my surprise, \NI discovered that these processes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.39,0:47:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,were not proven facts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.72,0:47:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,As a chemist, I’m fascinated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.79,0:48:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,by the distribution \Nof atoms within a molecule.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.93,0:48:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In living creatures, \Nthe 20 amino acids \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.33,0:48:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that are vital \Nfor the synthesis of life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.07,0:48:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic proteins \Nrequired for life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.14,0:48:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,interestingly, \Nare all levorotatory or left-handed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.81,0:48:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So when a ray \Nof polarized light arrives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.41,0:48:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,these amino acids \Ndivert the light toward the left. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.42,0:48:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no explanation for this \Nbecause the logical thing would be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.09,0:48:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that if this were a random process, \Nhalf would be right-handed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.03,0:48:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other half \Nwould be left-handed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.60,0:48:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked myself, ‘How could evolution \Nproduce compounds that are levorotatory\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.57,0:48:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and precisely the ones \Nessential for life?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.15,0:48:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, I had to conclude \Nthat there must be a force, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.88,0:49:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a Designer, a Creator of life \Nand of the elements \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.32,0:49:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and the amino acids \Nrequired for life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.02,0:49:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though \NI had a religious upbringing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.53,0:49:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,my ideas were not clear \Nas to who God was. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.46,0:49:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I merely viewed him \Nas a Supreme Being \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.53,0:49:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,before whom \Nwe would be held accountable.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.80,0:49:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible \Nis not a science textbook. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.97,0:49:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Its purpose is not to describe \Nthe universe we live in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.14,0:49:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,or the laws \Nthat regulate our universe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.65,0:49:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But when it does mention science, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.41,0:49:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and when it discusses scientific matters, \Nit does so with great accuracy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.35,0:49:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And undoubtedly the greatest benefit \Nis that it allows me to enjoy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.36,0:49:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a personal relationship \Nwith the Creator of the universe\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.59,0:49:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—a universe that fascinates me \Nfrom a scientific perspective.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.53,0:49:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Davey Loos. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.54,0:49:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I studied biochemistry \Nat the University of Leuven in Belgium, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.91,0:49:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and after that time \NI did a PhD in the same area.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.61,0:49:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a young child, \NI believed in the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.45,0:50:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But growing up, \NI kind of lost my interest in it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.72,0:50:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When you go to university \Nand you study life sciences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.62,0:50:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or biochemistry, for example,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.92,0:50:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you get introduced into the idea \Nof the origin of life very quickly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.63,0:50:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and also into the principle \Nof evolution.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.63,0:50:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The professors \Nwho taught these courses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.30,0:50:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,they were really scientists \Nwith long careers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.77,0:50:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were well-established scientists, \Nand we had a lot of respect for them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.97,0:50:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So there was just no way to really question\Nthe principle of evolution.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.74,0:50:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1999, there was a war \Nin Europe—in Kosovo—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.75,0:50:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and I remember reading \Nin the Bible as a child \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.95,0:50:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about the future events \Nthat would take place, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.76,0:50:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and I started wondering whether the war \Nin Kosovo was one of those events. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.53,0:50:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So that lead me \Nto pick up the Bible again.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.46,0:50:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time, I felt that I had to reexamine \Nmy beliefs about the origin of life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.70,0:50:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and also about the principle \Nof evolution.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.71,0:51:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on the theory of evolution, \Nwe would expect to see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.71,0:51:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,an abundance of transitional forms \Nto be present in the fossil record. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.88,0:51:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we do look at the fossil evidence,\Nwe just don’t see that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.18,0:51:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that the major species \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.69,0:51:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,come into existence \Nat specific times, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.19,0:51:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and their form and structure \Nis still exactly the same\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.96,0:51:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,as their form \Nand structure today.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.13,0:51:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was actually Darwin himself \Nwho wrote in his book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.63,0:51:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that the biggest objection \Nthat could be brought against this theory \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.70,0:51:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the fact \Nthat the fossil record \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.87,0:51:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,does not show an abundance \Nof transitional forms. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.81,0:51:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s what really happens \Nif you look at the set of data\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.05,0:51:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,—the fossil record seems to prove \Nthe opposite of evolution.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.82,0:51:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As a biochemist, \NI had the opportunity to learn about \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.22,0:51:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and study \Nmany different biomolecules. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.89,0:51:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I observed \Nthat pretty much every biomolecule \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.39,0:51:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is really a complex molecule. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.56,0:52:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We can look at them \Nas nanoscale molecular motors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.90,0:52:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or machines that are performing \Nvery complex and specific tasks.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.37,0:52:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For me, the complexity that we see in nature\Nand the complexity in those molecules \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.21,0:52:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,points to the fact \Nthat there really is a Creator.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.28,0:52:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see common ground \Nthat could help you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.95,0:52:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in your next discussion \Nwith someone who believes in evolution? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.72,0:52:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When Sister Picado Herrero’s \Nchemistry research \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.79,0:52:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,showed evidence of design,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.79,0:52:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,she called to mind her view of God \Nfrom her religious upbringing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.06,0:52:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The person you meet \Nwho believes in evolution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.67,0:52:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,might also have unanswered questions \Nabout God from their upbringing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.34,0:52:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they may respond \Nto the simple evidences\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.21,0:52:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of a Creator \Nthat you present. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.64,0:52:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Loos \Nwas moved by world events \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.58,0:52:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to pick up the Bible \Nand reexamine his beliefs.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.98,0:52:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone we meet, \Neven firm believers in evolution, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.65,0:52:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,are affected by world conditions \Nand may listen to our message of hope. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.66,0:53:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So when someone says \Nthat he believes in evolution, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.79,0:53:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t be quick to assume \Nthat he’ll reject the good news. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.00,0:53:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, our ministry \Nand other aspects of life often improve \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.74,0:53:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,when we slow down, \Ntake our time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.54,0:53:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and as our music video admonishes: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.14,0:53:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Don’t Run Fast.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.22,0:53:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You can walk, but please don’t run.\NIt’s hard to do when you’re having fun.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.79,0:53:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s a reason we don’t race;\NWhen you’re with the friends,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.87,0:53:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not the time or place.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.90,0:53:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t run so fast.\NTake your time and make things last.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.32,0:54:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn to love the things you do.\NJust don’t run fast.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.26,0:54:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve got things you have to do,\NPeople to serve, who depend on you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.51,0:54:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But don’t forget why you’re here;\NLearn to love the friends;\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.88,0:54:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them know you care.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.75,0:54:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t run so fast.\NTake your time and make things last.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.33,0:54:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn to love the things you do.\NJust don’t run fast.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.01,0:55:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can run to someone’s door.\NIs there someone home?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.85,0:55:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you’re not real sure.\NBut look around and see everyone,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.76,0:55:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,People walking by. Can you talk to one?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.43,0:55:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t run so fast.\NTake your time and make things last.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.78,0:55:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn to love the things you do.\NJust don’t run fast.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.26,0:55:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Just don’t run fast!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.47,0:56:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we shouldn’t run \Nat all in the Kingdom Hall. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.61,0:56:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But in a figurative sense, \Nthis counsel, not to run fast, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.08,0:56:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,applies to more \Nthan just our young ones. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.48,0:56:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,As we saw, even when we’re busy \Nwith important theocratic work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.02,0:56:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we can still take the time \Nto consider, incite, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.02,0:56:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and encourage our brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.16,0:56:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And rather than rushing \Nthrough our field service, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.16,0:56:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to imitate \NJesus’ focus on finding people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.50,0:56:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and reaching hearts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.57,0:56:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah reaches our hearts \Nin ever so many ways, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.84,0:56:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,such as when we attend \Nour spiritual gatherings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.91,0:56:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,By now, some of you \Nhave already attended \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.58,0:56:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the 2016 “Remain Loyal to Jehovah!” \Nregional convention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.98,0:56:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But millions of us still have \Nan exciting three days ahead \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.72,0:56:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with 47 well-prepared talks, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.32,0:56:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,18 songs that we’ll \Nsing to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.06,0:56:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and more than 50 audio \Nand video presentations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.39,0:56:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,including 2 feature-length dramas.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.16,0:56:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these program parts \Nhave been prepared to help us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.57,0:57:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,remain loyal to God \Ndespite serious challenges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.97,0:57:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, \Nhow can we maintain our loyalty \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.74,0:57:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when under stress or temptation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.34,0:57:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What did Jehovah \Npersonally teach Job \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.14,0:57:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that can strengthen \Nour loyalty? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.15,0:57:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And why does the Bible say \Nthat Jehovah’s loyal love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.88,0:57:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is more precious than life itself? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.95,0:57:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To find out more \Nof what you can expect, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.72,0:57:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,review the full convention program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.13,0:57:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,which can be downloaded \Nfrom jw.org. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.33,0:57:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You won’t want to miss any part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.46,0:57:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of the “Remain Loyal to Jehovah!” \Nconvention program!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.33,0:57:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As we close, \Nwe bring you greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.54,0:57:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Las Perlas-Ngäbere \Ncongregation in Panama. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.21,0:57:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The Volcán region \Nis the highest point in the country, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.11,0:57:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoying a cool climate \Nfor growing coffee \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.01,0:57:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and a variety of vegetables. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.08,0:57:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The busy harvest work \Nfrom October to December \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.82,0:57:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,brings large numbers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.09,0:57:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of Ngäbere-speaking people \Nto the area. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.09,0:58:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Their kind nature gives our brothers \Nexcellent opportunities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.56,0:58:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to teach them \Nabout God’s Kingdom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.63,0:58:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Local brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.63,0:58:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,provide regular support \Nto the Ngäbere Remote Translation Office. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.30,0:58:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And some are making the effort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.71,0:58:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn the language to assist \Nin the congregation’s spiritual harvest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.45,0:58:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We send them \Nour warm Christian love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.38,0:58:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and greetings in return and pray for them \Nto continue in their zealous spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.39,0:58:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank you and hope \Nyou’ve enjoyed our program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.73,0:58:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.83,0:58:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,from Brooklyn, New York!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.22,0:00:04.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,JW Broadcastingにようこそ!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.25,0:00:09.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のプログラムでは インド手話の区域で\N宣べ伝えている一人の兄弟にお会いします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.83,0:00:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その難しい割り当てに対する\N兄弟の見方から何を学べるでしょうか?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.27,0:00:17.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,羊はエホバに属しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.57,0:00:21.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,このドラマは ご自分の羊の\N群れを世話するために—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.10,0:00:25.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが会衆の牧者を特別な仕方で\N用いることを示しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.88,0:00:29.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,また あなたは初めて\N神の名前を知った人が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.15,0:00:33.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,生き方を変化させた瞬間を\N目撃したことがありますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.18,0:00:38.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の神を長年探し求めていたこの姉妹が\Nどうなったかを見てみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.52,0:00:42.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,2016年6月の\NJW Broadcastingから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.19,0:00:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに多くのことを\Nご覧いただけるでしょう！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.38,0:01:07.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの民は\N神の言葉を学ぶことが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.55,0:01:11.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,常に生活の重要な部分を\N占めるべきであると考えています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.39,0:01:17.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルに対する神の律法は その王が \N“命の日の限り [律法]を読まなければならない—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.66,0:01:22.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それは 自分の神エホバを恐れることを\N学ぶためである”と命じていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.73,0:01:25.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,メキシコのユカタン州の\Nマヤ語の区域では—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.74,0:01:30.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分で神の言葉を読むよう\N兄弟たちが地元の人々を援助しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.31,0:01:33.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を読めるようになると\N生活は変化し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.51,0:01:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,より早く“自分の神エホバを恐れることを\N学ぶ”ようになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.69,0:01:51.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,地球上の6人に1人は\N読み方を知りません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.46,0:01:53.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中のエホバの証人は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.76,0:01:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうした人々を助けるために\N識字クラスを組織しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.51,0:02:04.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,読むのは苦手です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.67,0:02:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会中は寝ていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.92,0:02:18.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの区域では たいていの人は\Nマヤ語を話しますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.29,0:02:21.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,読める人はほとんどいません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.29,0:02:25.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしが講演をして\N聖句を引用するときには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.09,0:02:28.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,聴衆はその聖句を見ますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.30,0:02:30.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,読めないので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.20,0:02:33.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぽかんとした顔をしているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.87,0:02:37.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとその言葉を学びたかったので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.14,0:02:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,読み方を学ぶようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.48,0:02:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,一人の姉妹が家に来て\N教えてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.15,0:02:52.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,識字クラスは個人のレベルに\N応じて開かれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.76,0:02:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書研究の後 少しの時間を使って\N読み方を練習します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.43,0:03:05.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,この訓練から益を受けることのできる人が\N大勢いることが長老たちに認められると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.54,0:03:10.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国会館でのもっと大きな\Nクラスが計画されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.87,0:03:13.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,この目的のために使用されるテキストは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.74,0:03:17.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,「読み書きに励む」というブロシュアーです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.08,0:03:23.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは中央アメリカ支部の管轄区域の\N30の言語で入手できます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.05,0:03:26.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,クラスに入っている生徒の\N助けになるのであれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.89,0:03:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの資料も使用することができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.33,0:03:36.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,発音の難しい言葉を黒板に書きます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.20,0:03:41.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは複雑な言葉を読む助けとなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.97,0:03:45.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても早く学ぶことの\Nできる人も幾人かいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.84,0:03:49.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,一方で 一語一語学ぶ人もいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.08,0:03:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 練習するにつれて\N正しく読むことを学び始めます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.05,0:04:02.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは石工の仕事は上手ですが\N読むのは苦手です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.89,0:04:06.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,この年齢で読むには努力がいります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.86,0:04:10.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,生徒の学び方が異なっている\Nことを理解すべきです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.33,0:04:14.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,人によっては とても辛抱強く\Nなければなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.24,0:04:20.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,書き方を学んだ最初の\N言葉は エホバでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.18,0:04:22.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,“こう書くんです”というと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.21,0:04:26.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,“辛抱強く教えてくれない\Nからだよ”と言われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.92,0:04:33.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユーモアのセンスは 間違いや失敗に\N注意を向けないための大きな助けです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.02,0:04:37.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,1946年にメキシコで\N記録を取り始めて以来—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.53,0:04:41.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,15万2千人以上が\N読み書きを学びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.13,0:04:43.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,払われた努力に感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.60,0:04:45.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,メキシコ州の教育長官は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.70,0:04:51.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,この識字クラスが地元市民に対して行なった\N仕事や大きな援助に感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.54,0:04:55.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,学んだスキルは日々の生活で\N助けとなっているだけでなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.38,0:04:57.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバについてさらに学び—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:05:02.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人を教えることができるように\Nなるための助けとなっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.82,0:05:06.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前は話すことを\N全部覚えましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.59,0:05:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では聖書から直接\N短い聖句を読むことができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.46,0:05:16.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,進歩するにつれて 生徒たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.67,0:05:23.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,テモテ第一 4:15の “あなたの進歩が\Nすべての人に明らかになるようにしなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.47,0:05:26.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,という聖句を実証する\Nことになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.28,0:05:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,クラスの益は生徒たちの中に\N明らかに見られます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.75,0:05:39.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,夫はアルコール中毒で たばこを吸い\N汚ない言葉を話していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.12,0:05:41.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 大きな変化を遂げました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.92,0:05:45.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,この訓練が大きな助けとなりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.43,0:05:49.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,すばらしい祝福です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.10,0:05:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:06:00.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,朗読の技術を改善するよう\N助けることができてとても幸福です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.41,0:06:07.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,情報を読んで理解することから来る\N喜びの表情を見ることができるのは最高です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.55,0:06:11.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな益を受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.19,0:06:15.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では家族で一緒に聖書を読めます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.86,0:06:19.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても幸せです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.36,0:06:22.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族が以前よりも一致しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.97,0:06:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,子どもたちは父親を敬っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.67,0:06:32.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,今 奉仕の僕です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.88,0:06:38.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,家から家の伝道に行くと\N“読めない”という人がいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.41,0:06:40.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも こう言います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:46.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしも読めませんでしたが\Nエホバについて学びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.39,0:06:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたもできます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.86,0:06:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしができたのですから\Nだれでもできます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.49,0:07:23.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のテーマは “ますます互いのことを\N考え 鼓舞し 励まし合う” です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.06,0:07:28.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんがJW Broadcastingを\Nとても楽しんでおられるのはなぜですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.53,0:07:31.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの皆さんは\Nおかげで兄弟姉妹や—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.67,0:07:35.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織を身近に感じる\Nようになれたと述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.87,0:07:41.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,家から出られず孤立しているなら\N特にこのプログラムは楽しみでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.28,0:07:45.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも こういう技術の進歩には\N感謝しつつも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.41,0:07:49.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんは会衆の集会に出席して\N兄弟姉妹と一緒になりたい—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.52,0:07:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,という誠実な願いを抱いて\Nおられることでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.69,0:08:00.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中のエホバの証人は\N同じように感じています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.06,0:08:05.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィンランド北部の冬は\Nとりわけ寒くなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.57,0:08:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,時にはー50℃まで下がります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.64,0:08:15.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,この状況では 運転をしたり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.08,0:08:19.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,ましてや長い距離を歩いたり\Nすることはとても困難です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.08,0:08:22.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも兄弟たちは集まることを\N楽しみにしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.75,0:08:24.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうするのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.55,0:08:28.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある小さな村の一人の兄弟は\N王国会館の近くに住んでいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.89,0:08:31.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,暖房の効くガレージを持っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.53,0:08:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会の晩に 兄弟は車で会衆の\Nそれぞれの家族を会館まで運びます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.00,0:08:41.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 車をガレージに止めて\N王国会館まで走って戻るのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.87,0:08:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会後 皆を家まで\N安全に送り届けます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.54,0:08:54.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書では 清い崇拝のために集まることは\N仲間との個人的な交わりの機会でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.12,0:08:58.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのためには指定された場所に\N出かけなければならず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.39,0:09:03.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,労力 犠牲 危険が伴いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:08.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,出エジプト記 34:24が述べていること\Nを考えてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.40,0:09:12.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,この節は すべての\Nイスラエルの男子が年3回—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.34,0:09:17.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムでの祭りのために集まるように\Nとの命令に関連しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.21,0:09:20.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは何を意味したでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.01,0:09:22.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,土地を守る男子が\N一人もいなくなるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.95,0:09:26.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,民は敵の攻撃にさらされるが\Nままになるのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:29.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎年 定期的に年3回—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.02,0:09:34.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,すべての者がエルサレムに集まる\Nといううわさが近隣諸国に広まるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:39.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵がやって来て イスラエルの村や都市を\N侵略するのではないでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.83,0:09:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,出エジプト記 34:24には\Nエホバの驚くべき答えがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.88,0:10:05.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです 欲することさえないのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.52,0:10:08.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはその約束を守られました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.62,0:10:15.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,西暦前1513年から西暦66年にいたる\Nまでの期間 この年3回の祭りの期間は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.67,0:10:22.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,どの諸国もイスラエルの領地を\N侵略しなかったことは歴史の事実です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.57,0:10:29.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはご自分の民が ずっと\N共に集まることを重視しておられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.41,0:10:35.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,クリスチャンの時代において\N使徒パウロはコリント第一 14:23で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.55,0:10:40.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,“会衆全体が一つの場所に集まる”\Nことについて書きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.29,0:10:44.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時は 現代のブロードキャスティングの\N技術はありませんでしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.86,0:10:49.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,手紙などの有効な手段がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.90,0:10:54.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際に同じ場所にいなくても\Nコミュニケーションをとることは可能でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.87,0:11:00.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒ヨハネは有能な筆者でしたが\Nヨハネ第二 12にあるように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.21,0:11:06.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間のクリスチャンと向かい合って\N交友を持つことのほうを好みました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.22,0:11:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,また ヨブ 1:6について\N考えてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.96,0:11:24.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨブ 2:1は 同様の別の日に\Nついて述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.20,0:11:25.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.84,0:11:29.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,あらゆるコミュニケーション手段を\N自由に活用できるにもかかわらず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.97,0:11:34.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは天の霊の被造物のために\N特別な日を定め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.18,0:11:37.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らがご自分の前に\N集まるようにされました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.81,0:11:39.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,明らかに聖書は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.55,0:11:45.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の仲間の僕たちとの定期的で個人的な\N交わりを持つことを励ましています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.35,0:11:50.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,現代の通信技術を利用して集まりに\N仮想参加できるのはうれしいことですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.83,0:11:54.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは兄弟たちと共にいることに\N取って代わるものではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.96,0:11:56.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.30,0:12:00.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは会衆と交わることが\N成し遂げる事柄のためです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.70,0:12:05.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 栄養価の高い価値ある\N霊的食物を得るだけのことではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.98,0:12:08.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会は知識を与えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.11,0:12:10.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,JW Broadcastingも同じです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.55,0:12:12.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会は励みを与えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.55,0:12:14.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,JW Broadcastingもそうです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.95,0:12:18.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間のクリスチャンの注解や\N心からの歌は築き上げます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.92,0:12:23.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,JW Broadcastingでも\N同様のことを聞くことができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.09,0:12:28.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 一緒になり 一か所に集まるときに\Nほかの人はこちらの声を聞き—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.13,0:12:33.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの心からの確信 笑顔\N握手によって励みを受けます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.14,0:12:38.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会は 兄弟姉妹のことを時間や\N注意や関心を払うに値する人々だと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.97,0:12:43.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが評価していることを\N示す機会を与えてくれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.18,0:12:46.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,だからこそ わたしたちは\N家から出られず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.38,0:12:52.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,孤独を感じている兄弟たちを訪問し\N彼らを愛していることを示すのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.79,0:12:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに 集会は特別な仕方で\N聖霊の影響の下にわたしたちを導きます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.46,0:13:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,啓示 2:7で 栄光を受けた\Nイエスは言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.21,0:13:19.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは 誘惑に抵抗し\N勇気を保ち 宣教に備え—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.22,0:13:25.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,健全な決定を下すことができるように\Nなる点で聖霊の助けが必要です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.19,0:13:30.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会は 楽しい交わり\N平和的な雰囲気 真のさわやかさ— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.86,0:13:36.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,連帯感 与える機会を提供しますし\Nエホバの聖霊を受けるための手段ですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.63,0:13:42.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに加えてもうひとつ 集会に出席する\Nさらに一層重要な理由があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.61,0:13:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,共に集まり合うための一番重要な理由は\N詩編 26:12に述べられています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:01.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです 個人として\N共に集まり合う主要な理由は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.59,0:14:04.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが受けるにふさわしい\Nものを差し出すためです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.99,0:14:08.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 賛美と栄光と崇拝です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.46,0:14:10.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会に出席するなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.60,0:14:14.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとみ子に近づきたいと\N願っていることを示すことになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.77,0:14:18.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,あふれるほどの愛のうちに\Nエホバはさらに多くの人が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.24,0:14:21.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分に仕え 生き続ける\Nように招いておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.74,0:14:26.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは永久に生きられるので\Nエホバとの関係も永続します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.05,0:14:29.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵対者は終わりのない希望を\N差し伸べることができないので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.49,0:14:34.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,利己心や誇り その他の消極的な傾向を\Nあおり 同じ部屋にいたり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.09,0:14:38.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ活動をしたりしていても\N人々を互いに孤立させています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.69,0:14:41.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,対照的に わたしたちの偉大な神は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.66,0:14:45.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々をご自分とみ子に\Nまた互いに引き寄せてくださり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.83,0:14:49.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスがヨハネ 17:21で\N祈ったように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.47,0:14:53.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが“みな一つになる”\Nようにしてくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.11,0:14:56.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは わたしたちが\N互いに一致するために—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.28,0:14:59.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,単に同じ場所に集まる\Nという行為ではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.48,0:15:03.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの人は スーパーに行ったり\Nスポーツイベントに出かけたり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.82,0:15:07.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,公共の乗り物に乗ったりして\N同じ空間を共有します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.76,0:15:11.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,集まることそれ自体が一致している\Nということではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.56,0:15:14.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,真のクリスチャン会衆の違いは何ですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.50,0:15:20.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘブライ 10:24, 25がその質問に\Nどう答えているか注目してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.07,0:15:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこには 神の霊感によって定められた\Nすべての集まりのための基準が見出せます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.79,0:15:47.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,“互いのことをよく考える”とは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.23,0:15:52.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,また “愛とりっぱな業とを鼓舞し合う”\Nとはどういう意味でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.03,0:15:55.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして どのように\N“互いに励まし合う”のでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.87,0:16:01.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,“考える”とは \N“関心を払う 注意を払う”という意味です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.78,0:16:05.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから “互いのことを\Nよく考える”には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.11,0:16:09.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,単に挨拶をする以上の関心を\N示さなければなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:13.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,また お互いがよく注意を払うなら\N鼓舞し合う備えができ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.79,0:16:17.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,お互いのために行動するよう促されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.09,0:16:19.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,これをどのように行なえますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.80,0:16:24.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,比較したり 兄弟たちに恥ずかしい\N思いをさせたりするのではなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.57,0:16:29.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間の心を元気付けることによって\N“互いに励まし合う”ことができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.51,0:16:33.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,できる限りそうするなら\N後はエホバの霊が働き—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.71,0:16:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちは励まされたと\N感じることでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.28,0:16:45.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の崇拝とは参加することであり\N行動が求められます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.39,0:16:53.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,その良い例は 兄弟姉妹が一緒に\N歌うときに与えたり得たりする励ましです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.63,0:16:56.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,2月の週日の集会で\N取り上げられましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.87,0:16:58.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤ 12章にあるように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.93,0:17:03.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,古代イスラエルでは\N時々コーラスが歌われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.17,0:17:07.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルの歌の多くは\N交唱形式 つまり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.01,0:17:11.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある歌い手たちにほかの歌い手たちが\N答え応じて歌う形式でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.85,0:17:14.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえば 詩編 106編は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.15,0:17:18.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ヤハを賛美せよ”または“ハレルヤ”\Nという言葉で始まり 終わっていますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:23.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに対して人々は\N“アーメン！”と答え応じます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.36,0:17:29.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 136編はコーラス同士が\N互いに呼応しあう形式になっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.50,0:17:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,コーラス同士が交互にこのような歌詞を\N歌い合うのを想像してみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.32,0:17:58.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,これが26節まで続くのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.79,0:18:02.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日まで 歌は\Nエホバの善良さに対する—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.20,0:18:05.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの気持ちを\N表わす手段となっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.80,0:18:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの深い気持ちを表現する仲間と\N一緒に歌えるのはうれしいことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.41,0:18:17.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では歌の多くが\Nオーケストラの伴奏になっているので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.28,0:18:23.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国会館での週日や週末の集会で\N一緒に歌えるのはうれしいことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.35,0:18:27.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい形式の週日の集会を\Nどのように楽しんでおられますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.79,0:18:32.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,プログラムの多くは聖書そのものを\N掘り下げるようになっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.39,0:18:36.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまで公の宣教の準備の\Nために用いてきた時間を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.20,0:18:40.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,一層野外奉仕で直面する状況に\N備えるために用いています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.44,0:18:44.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会は満足のいくペースで進みます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.47,0:18:49.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです JW Broadcastingは\Nすばらしい祝福です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.48,0:18:55.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中の兄弟たちに同時に話をして\N強めるための強力な道具です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.58,0:19:00.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 仲間の神の僕と共に\N会衆の集会において—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.49,0:19:06.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを崇拝するという経験に\N取って替わるものは何もありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.13,0:19:08.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会が終わって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.70,0:19:12.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,閉会の祈りのあと\N頭を上げるとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.57,0:19:19.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを愛し その主権を擁護している\N人々に囲まれているのを感じます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.34,0:19:25.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうした大切な益については\N2016年4月号の研究記事—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.01,0:19:29.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,「崇拝のために集まり合うべきなのは\Nなぜですか」で詳しく扱われています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.95,0:19:32.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月その記事を世界中で学びます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.59,0:19:38.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後10月には 人々を集会に招待する\Nための特別なキャンペーンが行なわれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.43,0:19:41.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだエホバの証人と定期的に\N交わっておられないなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.50,0:19:44.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいは自分の会衆から\N離れて旅行しているなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.53,0:19:49.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,jw.org を使って近くの\N集会場所を探してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.14,0:19:55.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバの証人について」「集会」そして\N「最寄りの会場を探す」をクリックするか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.44,0:19:59.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいはjw.orgのどのページでも\N一番下までスクロールして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.95,0:20:02.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,「集会に出席する」をクリックします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.82,0:20:07.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会に出席するなら\Nあなたは 考えたり鼓舞したり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.09,0:20:11.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,“その日が近づくのを見てますます\N互いに励まし合ったりする”とは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.09,0:20:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういうことかを経験なさるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.33,0:20:23.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,崇拝のためにクリスチャンの集会に集まって\N益を得るための重要な方法について考えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.14,0:20:27.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の集会に\N初めて出席した多くの人は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.44,0:20:31.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,神のお名前エホバがよく用いられて\Nいることに気づきます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.78,0:20:34.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,このライフ・ストーリーでは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.12,0:20:38.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ソテン・ユーエンがカンボジアの\N虐殺現場を生き残った後—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.15,0:20:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神のお名前について知ったときの\N感動について語ります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.93,0:20:50.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,大量殺りくが行なわれた\Nカンボジアのキリングフィールドで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.13,0:20:52.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは神に祈りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.50,0:20:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもその名前を知りませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.72,0:21:10.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだ幼かった頃 家族は引き離され—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.82,0:21:17.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは朝の5時から夜の9時まで\N水田で働かされました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.73,0:21:21.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の子どもたちが死んでいくのを見ると—\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.43,0:21:25.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,絶望的になって助けを\N叫び求めたくなるものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.70,0:21:28.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,次は自分だと思うからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.30,0:21:32.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもわたしは\N真の神がどこかにいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.14,0:21:36.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,切り抜けられるよう助けて\N下さると信じていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.61,0:21:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,1年後 わたしの家族は\Nカンボジアから逃れることにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.35,0:21:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,6-7か月程かけて\Nタイまで歩いて行きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.13,0:21:54.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは20人きょうだいでしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.06,0:21:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,生き残ったのは 4人だけでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.34,0:22:04.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしには目の不自由な伯母がいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.47,0:22:07.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつもわたしの肩につかまっていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.38,0:22:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある日 わたしたちは\N捕らえられてしまいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.01,0:22:14.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らが射撃を始めると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.62,0:22:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは伯母と共に地面に倒れこみ\N死んだふりをしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.36,0:22:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,起き上がったときには\N両親の姿はありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.33,0:22:31.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か月もジャングルで過ごしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.33,0:22:34.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,生き残るため 何でも食べました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.64,0:22:38.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,伯母のことも助けなければなりませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.11,0:22:42.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある日 食べ物を探すために\N遠くまで歩いてゆくうちに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.98,0:22:46.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,帰り道がわからなくなってしまいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.52,0:22:50.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな木の下で泣きはじめ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.12,0:22:53.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,空を仰いで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.29,0:22:56.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の神に祈りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.59,0:23:01.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブッダに祈るよう\N教えられて育ちましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.83,0:23:06.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,その晩は ブッダではなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.87,0:23:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の神に祈りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.14,0:23:18.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして “真の神よ\Nもしおられるのでしたらー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.88,0:23:23.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,“どうか助けてください\Nとっても怖いです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.22,0:23:27.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,“お腹も空いて 寒いんです”\Nと祈りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.09,0:23:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈り終わると 木の下で\N眠り込んでしまいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.06,0:23:38.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ついにわたしは \Nタイの難民キャンプに収容され—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.47,0:23:42.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族とも再会できました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.24,0:23:46.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,10年ほど難民キャンプで過ごした後—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.17,0:23:49.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,アメリカに渡りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.88,0:23:54.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして引き続き真の神を探し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.02,0:24:00.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾つかの教会に通いましたが\N何も理解できませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.59,0:24:06.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある日 学校から帰る途中で\Nヘロルドという男性に会いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.39,0:24:11.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,神について話しても良いかと\N尋ねられたので どうぞと言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.23,0:24:15.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は聖書を持っていたので\Nきっと良い人だと思ったからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.90,0:24:21.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の話を一生懸命に聴きましたが\Nよく理解できませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.74,0:24:25.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで彼はゆっくり話してくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.65,0:24:29.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたの名前は？”と尋ねられ\N“ソテン”と答えると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.85,0:24:33.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は “あなたはソテン\Nわたしはヘロルド—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.66,0:24:37.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,“神の名前はエホバ”と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.29,0:24:41.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の名前なんて\N考えたこともありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.26,0:24:45.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,その日以来 エホバのみ名を\N決して忘れませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.43,0:24:48.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,心に刻み込まれたからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.34,0:24:51.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘロルドは電話番号を教えてくれ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.27,0:24:54.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻が訪問するようにする\Nと言ってくれましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.48,0:24:56.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは引っ越してしまいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.98,0:25:03.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだ真理を学んではいませんでしたが\Nいつもエホバに祈っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.15,0:25:07.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,神のみ名について知ってから\N再び教会に行きましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.89,0:25:12.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,司祭は“天におられる父よ”\Nと呼びかけるだけで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.03,0:25:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのお名前をなおざりにしていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.00,0:25:17.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでわたしは手を挙げました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.37,0:25:20.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして “「天の父よ」と祈るとき—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.80,0:25:24.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,“なぜ「天の父 エホバよ」と\N呼びかけないのですか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.27,0:25:28.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,“神のお名前を用いない\Nのですか？”と尋ねました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.71,0:25:34.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,すると司祭は “神は あなたがここに\Nいるように強要したりはしない”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.22,0:25:38.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,“出ていったって構わないんだよ”\Nと言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.05,0:25:42.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らがエホバのお名前を\N使わないことが分かったので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.42,0:25:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはそこを去り\N二度と戻りませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.06,0:25:52.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,何年も経ってから\Nヘロルドに電話をしてみました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.93,0:25:57.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰も出なかったので\Nメッセージを残しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.51,0:26:01.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしのことを覚えていて\Nくれたらと思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.14,0:26:06.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,すると2週間後 ヘロルドが\N訪ねてきてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.85,0:26:13.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも その頃は夜に仕事をして\Nいたため日中は寝ていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.02,0:26:19.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでもヘロルドはあきらめずに\Nまた来てくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.46,0:26:25.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしも 訪ねてきてくれるよう\Nエホバに祈り続けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.80,0:26:31.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてある日 ついに\Nヘロルドと会うことができました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.87,0:26:37.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,声もでませんでした\Nそして涙がこみ上げてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.15,0:26:41.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの名前を教えてくれた人と\N再会できたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.72,0:26:45.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから一人の姉妹との\N聖書研究が始まり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.82,0:26:49.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的に進歩するよう助けられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.39,0:26:54.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちのことを顧みてくださる\N天の父のことを知るのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.66,0:26:57.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に喜びでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.57,0:27:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その方についてもっと\N知りたいと思うようになり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.00,0:27:05.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,“神はこれを好まれますか？\Nあれはどうですか？”などと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.01,0:27:07.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,色々な質問をしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.34,0:27:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国会館に行くとエホバのお名前が\N何度も用いられていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.28,0:27:16.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここだ！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.82,0:27:20.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここがわたしの居場所だと思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.82,0:27:25.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,2013年にバプテスマを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.06,0:27:31.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジャングルで共に生き残った\N伯母は 今でも健在です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.67,0:27:38.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてエホバについて伯母に\N話すことができるのは祝福です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.04,0:27:41.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の神がおられること—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.41,0:27:45.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,それがどなたかということを\N知ることができるのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.31,0:27:47.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に素晴らしい—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.05,0:27:49.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな特権だと感じています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.92,0:27:53.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,その方にはお名前があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.59,0:27:56.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,その名は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.36,0:27:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.57,0:28:11.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹は 冷酷な戦争によって\N自分や家族が味わった—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.67,0:28:14.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,痛ましい記憶を今も引きずっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.78,0:28:20.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 姉妹には将来の希望と天の父\Nエホバを知ることからくる慰めとがあり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.28,0:28:22.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはわたしたちも抱いているものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.98,0:28:25.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹は夫と幼い娘と共に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.55,0:28:30.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の神を崇拝できる増し加えられた\N喜びを味わっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.76,0:28:34.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会において 会衆は\N“一人の羊飼い”に従う—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.86,0:28:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“一つの群れ”として一緒に\Nとどまるように助けられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.00,0:28:43.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のドラマでは 一人の若者が\N忠実な従属の牧者を通して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.97,0:28:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのようにエホバの愛を示されたかに\N注目してみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.45,0:28:53.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,ずっと音楽が好きだった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.75,0:28:56.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギターを弾き始めたのは15歳のときで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.92,0:29:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それからは ギターで自分を表現してきた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.12,0:29:06.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,“デイブ バンドに入らないか？”\Nって声をかけられたときは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.09,0:29:09.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,迷わずに応じたよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.83,0:29:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,音楽を作ることが僕のすべてだった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.60,0:29:18.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミュージシャンになれば\Nきっと幸せになると思っていた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.64,0:29:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして その道を歩み続けてきたんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.05,0:29:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも現実は 思っていたのとは違っていた…\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.33,0:29:41.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,生活のために 日中はここで働いている\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.13,0:29:44.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の人生はもっと良くなる\Nと思っていたけど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.40,0:29:46.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か物足りなかった…\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.97,0:29:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,幸福になるどころか 何かを\N失っている気がしていたんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.35,0:30:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いけない 集中しなきゃ！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.36,0:30:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,感じのいい人たちだな\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.10,0:30:21.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼がパンフレットを差し出してこう言った\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.77,0:30:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの人は本当の幸福を探し求めています\Nあなたもそうではありませんか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.71,0:30:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けが得られそうだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.15,0:30:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに住所を書いて 仕事が終わった後に\N訪ねてきてくれないか聞いてみた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.67,0:30:54.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,確かに僕も 探し求めているんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.54,0:31:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際には 答えはいつも僕の\N目の前にあったのかもしれない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.44,0:31:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうして今まで気付かなかったんだろう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.12,0:31:14.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,実は…\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.96,0:31:17.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマを受けているんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.29,0:31:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 本当の意味で真理を\N受け入れてはこなかった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.00,0:31:31.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロイは約束どおり訪ねてきてくれた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.64,0:31:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで “自分はバプテスマを受けた\N兄弟です”って打ち明けた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.42,0:31:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロイは良く話を聞いてくれた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.85,0:31:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 詩編 100:3を\N開いてくれたんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.77,0:32:04.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の中で エホバは\N羊飼いに例えられている\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.57,0:32:07.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はすべての羊をご存じで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.08,0:32:10.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,一匹でもいなくなれば\Nすぐに気付かれるんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.95,0:32:14.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,いなくなっても\N見放されているわけじゃない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.62,0:32:17.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだ神に属する羊なんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.49,0:32:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはそれを見出すために\Nどんな努力も惜しまれない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.20,0:32:30.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕も失われた羊のひとりだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.10,0:32:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも今もエホバに属している\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.50,0:32:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 神は僕のことを\N忘れたりされなかった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.95,0:32:46.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロイはまた会おうと言ってくれた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.71,0:32:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして日曜日の集会に誘ってくれたんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.36,0:33:03.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,その朝は本当に緊張したよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.36,0:33:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,見栄えよくしていかないと\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.61,0:33:17.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロイとマシューが待っていてくれて\N温かく歓迎してくれた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.71,0:33:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことは絶対に忘れないよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.62,0:33:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,懐かしいな \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.12,0:33:30.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,これこそエホバの会衆だ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.26,0:33:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕の居場所はここにあるんだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.83,0:33:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理がこれほどはっきり\N理解できたことはなかった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.94,0:33:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹との親しい交わりは本当に楽しい\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.32,0:33:58.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,何より楽しいのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.12,0:34:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛ある父エホバを見出すよう\N他の人を助けることだ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.16,0:34:07.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに頼り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.70,0:34:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕はもう二度と 迷い出たりはしない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.71,0:34:21.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,2015年11月のブロード\Nキャスティングでは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.91,0:34:26.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの保護の み腕の中に勝る場所は\Nほかにないことが強調されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.81,0:34:29.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,今もエホバから漂い出た\Nままでいるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.92,0:34:33.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,遅れることなく行動するよう\N励ましたいと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.72,0:34:37.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドラマで見たように\Nエホバは羊を世話し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.13,0:34:43.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分の組織に戻るよう 愛ある仕方で\N導いてくれる羊飼いを備えておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.83,0:34:47.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,韓国などの国で宣べ伝える業\Nが始まったとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.24,0:34:52.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは兄弟たちを強めるために\N宣教者たちを用いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.41,0:34:54.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,アーカイブにあるインタビューの中で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.64,0:34:58.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,パク ジョンイル兄弟は\Nそれが自分の奉仕に与えた影響と—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.68,0:35:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,試練にどのように備えさせて\Nくれたかを説明しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.89,0:35:12.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,1939年以降 エホバの組織との\N連絡が途絶えたため—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.16,0:35:17.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちは もう組織は存在しない\Nと考えていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.50,0:35:21.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,ところが1948年に\N一人の兄弟が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.67,0:35:27.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,ものみの塔協会の活動に関する\N新聞記事を見つけました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.64,0:35:32.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちは驚いて 協会に\N手紙を書き送りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.71,0:35:35.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,協会は韓国からの知らせに喜び—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.88,0:35:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,韓国語の小冊子を送ってくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.66,0:35:44.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,反応は二つに分かれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.29,0:35:48.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教を再開することに\N興奮を覚える兄弟たちと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.13,0:35:54.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,これがエホバの用いる真の組織なのか\Nと疑う兄弟たちがいたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.90,0:36:02.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,1949年8月9日 宣教者の第一陣として\Nスティール兄弟姉妹が到着しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.94,0:36:07.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,スティール兄弟は わたしたちの質問\Nすべてに答えてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.95,0:36:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで兄弟たちはすぐに\N一致のうちに宣教に携わりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.02,0:36:19.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは1950年に開拓奉仕を始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.93,0:36:26.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ年の3月には ギレアデを卒業した\N宣教者がさらに6名到着しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.97,0:36:31.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時ソウルには会衆が\N一つしかありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.04,0:36:34.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教者たちはたくさんの\N聖書研究を司会していて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.41,0:36:39.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,関心を示した大勢の人々が\N集会に出席するようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.58,0:36:46.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 初めての試みとして小学校の\N講堂で公開講演が開かれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.55,0:36:49.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,伝道者は60名ほどでしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.56,0:36:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その日の公開講演には360名を\N超える人々が出席しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.14,0:37:06.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,その同じ日 朝鮮戦争が勃発しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.31,0:37:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教者たちは避難しなければならなくなり\N6月27日に日本に逃れました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.78,0:37:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの兄弟たちが\N韓国の南部に避難しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.63,0:37:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは市内に隠れていましたが\N数日後 共産党の秘密警察に見つかりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.40,0:37:38.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,クリスチャンなので\N戦争には参加できないこと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.01,0:37:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで隠れていたことを説明しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.78,0:37:50.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,すると警官は “わたしは宗教に\Nついてはよく知らないので—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.15,0:37:54.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,“宗教に詳しい友人を連れて\Nきたほうがよさそうだ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.59,0:38:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“明日もう一度来るので それまで\Nここを離れないように”と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.40,0:38:06.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして次の日 その警官は別の警官を\N連れてやってきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.97,0:38:13.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで わたしは聖書から証言し\N戦争や世界で生じている様々な問題が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.44,0:38:18.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 24章の預言の成就\Nであることを説明しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.71,0:38:27.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,すると彼らは“説明してくれてありがとう\Nそれじゃあ”と言って去っていきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.69,0:38:35.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,二日後 二人目の警官が別の友人を連れて\Nきたので また証言することができました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.53,0:38:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らがソウルに留まっていた3か月間\Nわたしたちは事実上彼らに守られました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.81,0:38:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 わたしは韓国軍に捕まりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.28,0:39:00.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 前線で戦う兵士をサポートする\N仕事を命じられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.05,0:39:04.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,武器を運ぶ仕事です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.49,0:39:07.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは受け入れられなかったので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.46,0:39:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その仕事を拒否しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.00,0:39:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,すると ひどく殴られました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.04,0:39:24.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある日のこと その部隊が別の場所に\N移動することになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.71,0:39:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは天井裏に身を隠しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.48,0:39:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆が移動する際に気付かれない\Nようにするためです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.99,0:39:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,次の朝 下に降りてみると\N部隊は移動した後でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.53,0:39:48.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから通りに出て\Nある方向に進んでいくと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.20,0:39:53.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,「国際聖書研究者協会」と\N書かれた看板が見えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.64,0:39:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはそこで 兄弟たちと\N共に6か月間過ごしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.01,0:40:04.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,後にスティール兄弟は\N仲間の兄弟たちを世話するため—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.55,0:40:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,独りで日本から戻って来られました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.56,0:40:14.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,1952年 兄弟はわたしを\Nギレアデ学校に推薦してくださり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.90,0:40:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,第22期のクラスに招待されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.50,0:40:22.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,ところが パスポートを取りに行くと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.44,0:40:26.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,政府はわたしが徴兵を終えて\Nいないことに気付きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.97,0:40:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは政府から パスポートの代わりに\N徴兵の通告書を受け取りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.32,0:40:42.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 中立の問題に直面することになり\Nギレアデ学校に行くかわりに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.26,0:40:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,軍の刑務所で2年間服役\Nすることになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.50,0:40:57.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,1958年 ギレアデ第32期\Nのクラスに入校しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.54,0:41:03.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校での素晴らしい訓練に\N本当に感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.88,0:41:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,支部では翻訳の仕事をしていますが\N翻訳作業には深い知識が不可欠です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.15,0:41:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギレアデでの訓練は その面でも\N大きな助けになっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.16,0:41:24.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理と組織に対する感謝や\N兄弟たちが示してくださる—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.17,0:41:29.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,謙遜さや温和さなどの特質に対する\N感謝や認識を培うことは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.20,0:41:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その手本に倣って全時間奉仕に\N打ち込む点で助けとなってきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.22,0:41:47.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,迫害と投獄と耐え忍んだ後—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.09,0:41:50.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,パク兄弟は何に一番感謝\Nしていたでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.82,0:41:57.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちが示したキリストのような人格と\Nエホバの組織から受けた訓練です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.36,0:42:02.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは 共に集まることがもたらす\N益のもう一つの例です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.07,0:42:06.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,パク兄弟の信仰に倣うための方法に\Nついてさらに知りたいなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.54,0:42:10.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,2008年12月号の「目ざめよ！」誌\N12ページから始まる—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.48,0:42:13.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ライフ・ストーリーをご覧ください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.61,0:42:16.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,年長の人たちのように\N若い兄弟姉妹たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.92,0:42:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的にやりがいのある\N割り当てに取り組んでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.29,0:42:26.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,次はインドに行って フランシス・\Nロドリゲス兄弟から話を聞きましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.26,0:42:30.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は 王国福音宣明者のための\N学校の訓練を活用して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.97,0:42:34.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,インド手話の区域で人々を教えています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.64,0:42:39.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,若いころ 近くの会衆に\N二人の特別開拓者がいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.27,0:42:42.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにお仕えする\N幸福な姿を見ていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.98,0:42:46.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,海外で仕事をするという\N選択肢もありましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.48,0:42:50.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに全時間お仕えすることにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.22,0:42:55.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,特別全時間奉仕をしていると\Nエホバが必要を顧みてくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.29,0:43:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神のみ手にある有用な道具として\Nどこでも用いて頂きたいと願っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.10,0:43:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,一年前から インド手話の\N畑で奉仕しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.17,0:43:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕されていない\N20ほどの区域を訪問しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.28,0:43:19.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,朝7時から ろう者を探す業を始めます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.75,0:43:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,村人の大半は農業をしていて\N休憩のために帰ってきます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.56,0:43:32.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,夜の9時か9時半頃まで奉仕します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.83,0:43:35.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから夜のうちに次の村に移動し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.56,0:43:38.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,朝7時には聖書研究を始めます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.77,0:43:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これを週に4回行ないます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.57,0:43:46.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,記念式の招待活動を行なっていた\N区域に ろう学校がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.81,0:43:52.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,何人かの生徒が走り寄ってきて\N“エホバ 愛”と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.15,0:43:56.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは どうしてわたしたちを\N知っているの？と尋ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.12,0:44:01.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,すると 一度だけ集会に来たことのある\N少年がいることに気付きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.19,0:44:03.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼が学校の友達に話したんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.92,0:44:06.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,子どもたちは \N“一度ここにきて—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.53,0:44:10.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバについてもっと\N教えてください”と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.43,0:44:14.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校に一度も通ったことのない\Nろう者ともお会いします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.54,0:44:17.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういう場合 両親にも\N一緒に座ってもらって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.87,0:44:20.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,互いにコミュニケーション\Nを図る様子を観察し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.64,0:44:23.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らの手話に合わせる\Nようにしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.01,0:44:25.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,10時間ほど離れたある区域で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.78,0:44:29.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初に関心を示したのは\N2,3人のろう者だけでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.78,0:44:32.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 徐々に増え始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.49,0:44:37.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,朝7時から聖書研究を始めましたが\N代わる代わる人が来て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.19,0:44:42.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,10人から12人のグループで\N研究を行なうこともありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.93,0:44:46.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,夜の8時半には研究を\N終えなければなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.87,0:44:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,帰宅するために列車で\N10時間かかるからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.91,0:44:55.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,支部事務所を訪問する\N計画を立てました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.14,0:44:59.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,見学が終わると二人のろう者の\N少女が泣き始め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.01,0:45:02.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ここにいる兄弟たちから愛を示されて—” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.05,0:45:06.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバだけが真の神だ\Nとわかった”と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.22,0:45:09.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから二人の生活に\N変化が生じ始め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.39,0:45:13.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,一人はバプテスマを受けていない\N伝道者になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.23,0:45:17.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ろう者が自分たちの生活を\N変化させ 幸せになり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.90,0:45:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの良い関係を築いている\N様子を見ると 幸福になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.54,0:45:26.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,この割り当てには\N困難も伴います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.94,0:45:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,村を訪問するために 10時間もかけて\N移動すると疲れを感じます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.25,0:45:37.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,列車が満員のこともあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.15,0:45:40.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,帰りの列車が3時間も遅れる\Nことだってありますし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.59,0:45:43.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,列車が来ないこともあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.99,0:45:47.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,困難は生じますが\Nやがて過ぎ去ります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.69,0:45:50.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに気を取られない\Nようにしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.30,0:45:55.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは 困難を取り除くことではなく\Nそれを克服する力を祈り求めます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.87,0:46:00.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな困難も 経験できる益に\N比べれば取るに足りません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.51,0:46:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに焦点を合わせれば\N自分の割り当てを楽しめます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.45,0:46:10.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロドリゲス兄弟は困難があっても\Nできるときにはいつも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.85,0:46:15.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠の命のために正しく整えられた\N人々を見出そうとしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.82,0:46:19.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟の喜びは真の霊的\N兄弟関係に入るよう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.89,0:46:23.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々を会衆に導き入れる\Nことから来ています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.36,0:46:30.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中の伝道者や開拓者が勤勉な努力を\N払って同様に人々を導いています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.34,0:46:34.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに多くの人々がエホバとの\N良い関係を築くよう助けるために—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.98,0:46:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の宣教を吟味してみるのは\Nいかがでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.11,0:46:41.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,今このプログラムで見たように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.45,0:46:45.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰の模範は様々な形で\N示されることが分かります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.82,0:46:48.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,2016年4月のプログラムで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.82,0:46:54.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,「生命の起源に対する見方」という\Nシリーズの最初の二つの連載を見ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.06,0:46:57.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここで 科学を研究した\Nことのある人々が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.40,0:47:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,創造者に対する強い信仰を培った 二つの\N実例をさらに見ることにしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.58,0:47:11.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはロシーオ・ピカド・ヘレロです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.41,0:47:16.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,スペインのサラマンカ大学で\N化学を学びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.78,0:47:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,有機化学を専攻しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.42,0:47:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,炭素原子を中心に それに由来する\Nあらゆる化合物を研究します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.20,0:47:32.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは生命は進化によって\N生じたと信じていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.67,0:47:38.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,異なる脊椎動物の胎芽を描いた\N自然科学の本の写真を見て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.54,0:47:43.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,成長の初期段階で際立った類似性が\Nあったのを覚えています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.91,0:47:49.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,大学で研究を始めてから 進化理論の\N過程を詳細に学び始めましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.78,0:47:55.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,驚いたことに これらの過程は\N証明された事実ではありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.32,0:48:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは化学者として 分子内における\N原子の分布に非常に関心がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.33,0:48:09.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,生物には 生命の合成のために必要な\N20のアミノ酸があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.04,0:48:12.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,それらは生命に必要な\N基本タンパク質ですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.41,0:48:18.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深いことに そのすべては左旋回\Nつまり左利きなのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.18,0:48:24.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで偏光の光線が当たると\Nそれらのアミノ酸は光を左側にそらせます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.18,0:48:27.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしこれが成り行きで\N生じるのであれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.05,0:48:32.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,半分は右利きで あとの半分は左利きになる\Nというのが理論的な考え方で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.73,0:48:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしても説明がつきません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.10,0:48:41.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう自問しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.17,0:48:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,進化によって どのように生命に必要な\N左旋回の物質が合成できるのだろうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.55,0:48:56.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,ついにわたしは 力ある方 \N設計者 生命の創造者—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.42,0:49:02.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,また命に必要な物質やアミノ酸を作られた方が\Nおられるに違いないと結論しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.89,0:49:05.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,宗教的な環境で育ったものの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.49,0:49:10.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,神とは誰かに関してははっきりとした\N考えを持っていませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.26,0:49:15.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,言い開きをしなければならない\N至高者としか見ていませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.74,0:49:18.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は科学の教科書ではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.51,0:49:24.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはこの宇宙や宇宙を制御している法則を\N説明するための本ではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.81,0:49:28.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも科学や科学的なことを\N述べる点で 非常に正確です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.98,0:49:31.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 間違いなく最大の益は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.82,0:49:36.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書が 科学的な見地からして\Nわたしを魅了してやまない宇宙の—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.32,0:49:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,創造者との個人的な関係を\N楽しめるようにしてくれることです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.67,0:49:50.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはデイビー・ルースです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.04,0:49:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベルギーのルーヴェン大学で生化学を\N学び 博士号も取得しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.94,0:49:59.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,子どものころは聖書を\N信じていましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.95,0:50:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,成長するにつれて関心は\N薄らいでいきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.75,0:50:08.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,大学で生命科学や生化学を\N学び始めると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.52,0:50:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに生命の起源や進化論に\Nついて教えられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.83,0:50:19.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,教えている教授たちは 長年の経験と\N地位のある科学者たちばかりで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.53,0:50:21.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々から尊敬されてもいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.80,0:50:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 進化論について疑問を差し挟むこと\Nなど考えられませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.58,0:50:33.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,1999年 コソボ紛争がおきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.51,0:50:36.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは 子どもの頃に\N読んだ聖書の中に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.42,0:50:40.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,将来起きる出来事が予告されて\Nいたことを思い出しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.62,0:50:44.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,コソボでの紛争もその中の一つ\Nなのではないかと思うようになり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.89,0:50:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,再び聖書を手に取りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.30,0:50:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 生命の起源や進化論に関しても\N自分の信条を再吟味すべきだと感じました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.84,0:51:01.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,進化論が正しいとすれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.07,0:51:05.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,化石の記録の中には進化の課程にあるものを\Nたくさん見出せるはずです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.85,0:51:10.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 化石の証拠を調べてみても\Nそれは見出せませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.95,0:51:14.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,主だった種は ある特定の時に\N存在するようになり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.49,0:51:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その形や構造は今日に至るまで\N変わっていません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.76,0:51:24.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際 ダーウィン自身も\N自らの本の中で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.16,0:51:27.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,進化論に対して最も大きな\N異論を唱えるのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.73,0:51:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,化石の記録に進化の途上にあるものを\N見出せないという事実だろうと書いています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.41,0:51:37.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際に記録をたどっていけば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.81,0:51:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,化石の記録は進化論とは反対のことを\N示していることがわかります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.92,0:51:51.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,生化学者として 数多くの異なる生体分子を\N調べ 研究してきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.36,0:51:56.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして それらの生体分子が本当に\N複雑な分子であることがわかりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.83,0:51:59.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,極めて複雑な動きをする—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.40,0:52:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ナノスケールの分子モーターを\N観察すればそのことは明らかです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.71,0:52:09.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,自然界や分子の中に見られる\N精緻な造りは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.41,0:52:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,創造者が確かにおられる\Nことを証ししています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.42,0:52:20.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,進化を信じている人との話し合いに\N役立つ土台を見出せましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.39,0:52:25.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ピカド・ヘレロ姉妹が化学を探求して\N設計者がいる証拠を見つけたとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.56,0:52:29.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,子どもの時に神について考えていた\N事柄を思い出しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.93,0:52:33.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,進化を信じている人も\N幼い時から持っていた—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.20,0:52:36.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に関する答えの出ていない\N疑問を持っているかもしれず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.97,0:52:40.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが創造者に関する\N分かりやすい証拠を示すなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.34,0:52:42.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,答え応じるかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.48,0:52:48.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,ルース兄弟は 世界の出来事を見て\N自分の信仰を再吟味しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.35,0:52:50.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,強固な進化論者を含めて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.55,0:52:54.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,すべての人は世界の状況の\N影響を受けているので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.05,0:52:57.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,希望の音信に耳を傾けるかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.39,0:52:59.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 進化を信じている人でも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.95,0:53:03.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,良いたよりを聞かないと\N早急に結論しないでください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.73,0:53:07.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際 ペースを緩めたり\N時間をとったりするなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.13,0:53:10.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,物事は改善することは\N少なくありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.30,0:53:14.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のミュージックビデオは\N次のように勧めています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.31,0:53:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“走らないで”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.68,0:53:28.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるこう はしらずに\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.79,0:53:32.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,おもいきり はしゃぎたいよね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.39,0:53:36.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,だけど かんがえよう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.33,0:53:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなのこと たいせつに\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.97,0:53:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,はしらないで\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.91,0:53:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あいを まなぼう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.99,0:54:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっと できるよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.46,0:54:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,はしらないで\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.40,0:54:15.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,役に立ちたくて\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.17,0:54:19.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,目もくれず 前に向かう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.57,0:54:23.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,だけど 思い出そう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.38,0:54:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,君がいるのは 友のため\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.92,0:54:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あせらないで\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.69,0:54:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛を つなごう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.73,0:54:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっと 変わるよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.24,0:54:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あせらないで\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.35,0:55:02.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,家から家に\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.62,0:55:06.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,いそぐけど 返事はない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.45,0:55:10.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,だけど 立ち止まろう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.22,0:55:16.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,人はいるよ すぐそこに\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.73,0:55:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いそがないで\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.90,0:55:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛を 広げよう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.95,0:55:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっと 届くよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.42,0:55:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いそがないで\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.13,0:55:48.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,Oh \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.53,0:55:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いそがないで\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.80,0:56:01.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国会館の中では\N走ってはなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.04,0:56:05.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 比ゆ的な意味で\N早く走らないようにとのこの助言は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.61,0:56:08.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,若者だけに当てはまる\Nものではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.42,0:56:11.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,重要な神権的な業に忙しい時でも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.65,0:56:16.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,考え 鼓舞し 兄弟たちを励ますためにも\N時間を取ることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.79,0:56:20.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,野外奉仕において急いで\N区域を回るよりも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.13,0:56:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々を探して心に達することに努めた\Nイエスに見倣いましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.00,0:56:29.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは 多くの方法でわたしたちの\N心を動かしてくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.74,0:56:34.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,すでに2016年「エホバに\N忠節を保ちましょう！」地区大会に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.74,0:56:37.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,出席した人もおられるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.24,0:56:39.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも わたしたちの多くは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.48,0:56:43.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,興奮を誘う三日間を これから\N楽しむことになっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.58,0:56:46.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,47の良く準備された話—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.29,0:56:48.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに歌うための18曲の歌—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.99,0:56:51.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,50以上のオーディオと\Nビデオのプログラムー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.76,0:56:55.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして2つの長編ドラマが提供されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.03,0:56:57.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらのプログラムすべては—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.20,0:57:02.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,難しい問題があっても神に忠節を保つのを\N助けるために準備されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.50,0:57:07.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば ストレスや誘惑にあったとき\Nどのように忠節を保てるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.94,0:57:10.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはわたしたちの忠節を強める—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.48,0:57:13.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなことをヨブに個人的に\N教えられたでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.91,0:57:16.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜ聖書は\Nエホバの忠節な愛は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.68,0:57:20.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,命そのものよりも尊い\Nと述べているのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.19,0:57:25.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに多くの益を得るために\N大会のプログラム全体を概観してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.53,0:57:29.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはjw.org から\Nダウンロードできます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.53,0:57:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「 エホバに忠節を保ちましょう！」\N大会のどの部分も逃したくはないでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.17,0:57:40.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後に パナマのラス・ペルラス・ヌベレ\N会衆からのあいさつをお送りします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.97,0:57:44.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,ボルカン地区は\N国で最も高地にあり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.01,0:57:49.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,涼しい気候のため\Nコーヒーや様々な野菜が育ちます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.65,0:57:56.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,収穫の最盛期である10月から12月には\Nヌベレ語を話す大勢の人々がやってきます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.69,0:57:59.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,親切な気質の人々なので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.23,0:58:04.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちはこの素晴らしい機会を活用して\N神の王国について教えています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.60,0:58:06.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,地元の兄弟姉妹たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.60,0:58:10.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヌベレ語遠隔翻訳事務所を\N定期的にサポートしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.54,0:58:12.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,その言語を学ぶ努力を払い—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.91,0:58:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の霊的収穫を援助している\N兄弟たちもいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.15,0:58:24.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちからの温かいクリスチャン愛\Nとあいさつをお返しし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.45,0:58:29.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちが熱心な霊を保って\N励むよう祈りたいと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.06,0:58:32.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のプログラムを\N楽しまれたことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.59,0:58:37.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニューヨーク市 ブルックリンから\NJW Broadcastingでした\N
